// .claude/settings.local.json.example
//
// This is a TEMPLATE. Copy to .claude/settings.local.json and edit. The real
// file is gitignored — never commit it.
//
// This file is NOT loaded by Claude Code (only settings.local.json is). It
// exists purely as a reference so contributors know what knobs are available.
//
// PROJECT-WIDE POLICY lives in .claude/settings.json (committed). Anything you
// add here merges with — or in some cases overrides — that policy, for you
// only on this machine.
//
// SECURITY:
//   - Never put secrets, API keys, or keypair material in this file.
//   - Do NOT add patterns to "permissions.allow" that would match state-
//     mutating commands. The PreToolUse hook
//     (.claude/hooks/block-mutating-commands.mjs) will block them regardless,
//     but adding such patterns is a code smell and a sign you're trying to
//     bypass the workflow rule.
//   - Do NOT add "sandbox.autoAllowBashIfSandboxed: true". The committed
//     policy is allowlist-first (autoAllowBashIfSandboxed: false). Flipping
//     it true on your machine reverts you to the pre-Phase-0 permission model
//     and is not supported.
//
// Strip the comments before saving as JSON — Claude Code's parser does not
// accept JSONC.

{
  "permissions": {
    // Bash patterns you've personally pre-approved (auto-execute without
    // prompting). Project-wide allows are in committed settings.json; add
    // here only for things specific to your workflow.
    "allow": [
      // "Bash(docker ps)",
      // "Bash(docker logs *)",
      // "Bash(open *)"           // macOS: open files/URLs in default app
    ],

    // Patterns you want to hard-deny on your machine in addition to the
    // committed denies. Useful if you want to be extra strict locally.
    "deny": [
      // "Bash(open https://*)"   // example: prevent the agent from opening URLs
    ]
  },

  // Per-developer env vars passed to tool invocations. Never put secrets
  // here — use your shell environment instead.
  "env": {
    // "BALLAST_LOG_LEVEL": "debug"
  },

  // Per-developer hooks. Useful for personal niceties like desktop
  // notifications when the agent finishes a turn.
  "hooks": {
    // "Stop": [
    //   {
    //     "hooks": [
    //       {
    //         "type": "command",
    //         "command": "osascript -e 'display notification \"Claude done\" with title \"Ballast\"'"
    //       }
    //     ]
    //   }
    // ]
  }
}
